To run the CSVM with PSO:

go to ./testers and inspect bandit.py
Here the settingsfile can be eddited.

to run the csvm in PSO, execute start.sh in the /testers/ folder.

Notes on the settingsfile:

PatchSize MUST be an even number (patchsize % 2 == 0)

Types of similarity function for Codebook: (SimilarityFunction)
SOFT_ASSIGNMENT,
RBF
In both cases a value for similaritySigma must be set, 
although it is only used for the RBF similarity measure.

Types of SVM kernels: (Kernel)
LINEAR,
RBF,

Types of SVM's (Type)
CLASSIC,
CONV,